<h3 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h3>
<p>To answer these questions, we must translate this problem into a mathematics problem. With this in mind, suppose the height of the ball is given by <span class="process-math">\(y=y(t)\)</span> where <span class="process-math">\(y\)</span> is measured in meters and <span class="process-math">\(t\)</span> is measured in seconds.  Then we have the following information <span class="process-math">\(\dfdxn{y}{x}{2}=-9.8\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}^2}\text{,}\)</span> <span class="process-math">\(\eval{\dfdx{y}{x}}{t}{0}=19.6\frac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}\text{,}\)</span> and <span class="process-math">\(y(0)=2\text{m}\text{.}\)</span></p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-3.html#p-29" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
